<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-456-900  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 456 900.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computers in Banking  May 1990 v7 n5 p88(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Portfolio accounting software is big in size, power, complexity:portfolio manager aids reporting. (Shaw Data Services Inc'sMicroshaw) (Software Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Milliman, David M.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Shaw Data Service's Microshaw accounting software package, pricedat $4000, is an extremely flexible system appropriate forinvestment management and custom billing.andP;  The program runs on amicrocomputer and is menu-based.andP;  It provides several methods ofgauging the management performance of investment officers and ofcomparing portfolios to national indices.andP;  Through a modemMicroshaw provides connection to stock quotation services that canreprice issues.andP;  Shaw Data services can also create an optionalprogram to automatically enter all customer data into anothercomputer for safekeeping accounting.andP;  There are nine basic reportthemes and a generator to build custom reports.andP;  Disadvantages arethe system's size and complexity.andP;  An investment firm usingMicroshaw would need to hire at least a part-time employee toserve as fully trained operator, and the program calls for a fastmicrocomputer, IBM PC/XT or compatible, for satisfactory results.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Shaw Data Services, Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Microshaw (Accounting software).andO;Topic:     Investment BrokerageEvaluationSoftware ComplexityFinancial SoftwareAccounting.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>